main event: A UFO sighting in Elba, New York on 19th September 1950 witnessed by a couple at their home on Main Street. The object appeared like a star but moved rapidly, changed direction quickly, and vanished after about 30 minutes.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on September 19, 1950, and the object was observed for about 30 minutes before disappearing.
The object was initially mistaken for a star but was noted to move rapidly, change direction quickly, and unlike any known aircraft.
The witnesses, Mr. and Mrs. Wagner, described the object as moving very fast and unlike any aircraft they had ever seen.
The report suggests that the object did not exhibit blinking lights and followed an airline path.
The Inspector General USAF 13th District Office of Special Investigation acknowledged the letter from Mrs. Elizabeth Wagner and thanked her for reporting the observations.
witnesses: Civilian couple, Mr. and Mrs. Wagner
